item.title: Enel Outlines 2024-26 Strategy
item.description: Enel said it plans to boost investments in grids and refocus its renewables strategy while boosting cash generation and cutting costs as part of its plan for the 2024-26 period.

item.title: Thyssenkrupp Posts Net Loss With Sales Below Expectations
item.description: Thyssenkrupp reported net loss for the fourth quarter and its fiscal year on a tougher market that included higher costs and lower earnings at Steel Europe.

item.title: German Bund Yields Expected to Fall in 2024
item.description: G​erman Bund yields have potential to fall in 2024 as interest-rate cuts will intensify in the second half of next year, DZ Bank Research said, lowering its year-end yield forecast for 2024 to 2.2% from 2.4%.

item.title: Enel to Sell Peruvian Power Generation Assets
item.description: Enel has agreed to sell its Peruvian power generation assets to Niagara Energy for a total consideration of about $1.4 billion.

item.title: Nikkei Rises 0.3% on JPY Weakness, Likely Position Adjustment
item.description: Japan’s Nikkei Stock Average rose 0.3% to close at 33451.83 amid JPY weakness and likely position adjustment ahead of Thursday’s holiday in the U.S. and Japan.

item.title: How Walmart Is Leveraging Automation and AI to Deliver Faster
